
For Loop
========

. The Javascript for loop interates the elements for the fixed number of times.
. It should be used if numer of iteration is known. 

//syntax

for (initialization; condition; iteration;)


=> initialExpression: 
   The initialExpression executes once while entering the loop.

=> condition: 
   Checked before every loop iteration. If false, the loop is stop. 

=> iteration:
   Executes after the body on each iteration.

//example

for(let i = 1; i <= 5; i++){
    console.log(i) 
}
console.log("done")

//output

1
2
3
4
5
Done
